HEADWORD: Swingel
<hw>Swin"gel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>swingele</ets> whip, scourge. See <er>Swing</er>.]</ety> <def>The
swinging part of a flail which falls on the grain in thrashing; the
swiple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

